(Fee Policy and Deflation Dynamics) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(Atho?s fee floor is 500 atoms/vB, with a minimum transaction fee of 200,000 atoms. Fees are) Tj
T*
(split by deterministic routing rules that vary by regime:) Tj
T*
(- pre-tail: 40% of fees routed to consensus pool,) Tj
T*
(- post-tail: 55% of fees routed to consensus pool.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(In post-tail conditions, the non-pool portion is burn-routed under active policy constraints,) Tj
T*
(subject to supply-floor clipping behavior. At full utilization under current assumptions, annual) Tj
T*
(burn capacity can exceed annual tail issuance. This is why Atho?s modeled neutral utilization) Tj
T*
(threshold is around 24.802%: above that level, protocol-level net supply pressure becomes) Tj
T*
(deflationary until floor constraints become the limiting factor.) Tj
T*
() Tj
T*
(This is an important investor concept. Atho is not ?always inflationary? and not ?always) Tj
T*
(deflationary.? It is utilization-sensitive and policy-bounded. That makes the model more) Tj
T*
(realistic than static labels.) Tj
